# Writing Engine — environment configuration
#
# The default demo (`npm run demo`) and benchmark (`npm run benchmark`) run
# entirely on deterministic local fixtures and require NONE of these values.
# They are placeholders for the replaceable production ports (see docs/architecture.md).
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in only what you wire up.

# --- Runtime data store ---
# Directory for filesystem JSON persistence (gitignored). Defaults to ./data.
WRITING_ENGINE_DATA_DIR=./data

# --- Source adapter selection ---
# "fixture" (default, offline) | "live" (not yet implemented — see LiveSourceAdapter TODO)
SOURCE_ADAPTER=fixture

# --- Live feed (production port; not implemented in the scaffold) ---
# Example: a Texas open-data streaming endpoint or an Apify actor dataset.
# LIVE_FEED_URL=
# APIFY_TOKEN=
# APIFY_ACTOR_ID=

# --- Model inference (production port; not implemented in the scaffold) ---
# vLLM / Nemotron OpenAI-compatible endpoint for the production writer/evaluator.
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000/v1
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# WRITER_MODEL=nvidia/nemotron-...
# EVALUATOR_MODEL=nvidia/nemotron-...

# --- Persistence backend (production port; not implemented in the scaffold) ---
# Supabase project for durable run/rubric/source/lesson history.
# SUPABASE_URL=
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# --- Runtime security (production port; not implemented in the scaffold) ---
# HiddenLayer Runtime Security API for scanning sources, prompts, outputs, tool calls.
# HIDDENLAYER_API_KEY=
# HIDDENLAYER_EVENT_CODE=AITX-2026
